Depends: perl, nftables, jq, postgresql-client, libconfig-tiny-perl, libdbi-perl, libdbd-pg-perl, libjson-perl, libnet-cidr-perl, liblog-log4perl-perl, libfile-readbackwards-perl, libfile-slurp-perl, libregexp-common-perl, libwww-perl
Description: Distributed IP blocking system with centralized database (ALPHA)
 Bad IPs monitors system logs for malicious activity and automatically blocks
 offending IP addresses using nftables. Features centralized PostgreSQL database
 for correlation across multiple servers.
 .
 ALPHA STATUS: This software is currently in alpha testing. While actively
 tested on live production servers, use with appropriate caution.
 .
 Features:
  - Real-time log monitoring with systemd journal integration
  - Multi-threaded async architecture with queue-based pipeline
  - Centralized PostgreSQL database for cross-server correlation
  - Configurable per-service attack pattern detection
  - Never-block CIDR filtering for trusted networks
  - Automatic expiration and cleanup of stale blocks
  - Fast local blocking with <1ms response time
